\chapter{RESULT AND DISCUSSION}

The implementation of the PostalAI system has produced significant results. After comprehensive testing, the system demonstrated stable performance, robust data integrity, and seamless integration between the Flask web framework and the EasyOCR processing engine, utilizing MySQL for efficient data management. The automated workflow for pincode extraction, real-time sorting logic, and role-based user management proved to be highly effective in aiding the decision-making of postal administrators and streamlining the tasks of operational staff.
The automated sorting pipeline allowed users to upload parcel images, process them for pincode identification, and assign them to the correct virtual bins with minimal manual intervention. The deployment of this system on a secure server architecture ensured reliability, data integrity, and scalability, meeting the critical performance benchmarks for processing image batches as set during the planning phase.
Feedback from administrators and operational staff has been overwhelmingly positive. Users reported a significant reduction in manual sorting time, ease of processing batches of parcels, and the intuitive nature of managing staff and sorting bins. The system’s role-based access control effectively secured sensitive administrative functions while maintaining accessibility for authorized personnel. The core integration of EasyOCR and OpenCV was instrumental in automating the data extraction process, providing actionable sorting data and drastically reducing the potential for human error.

